last_episode_to_air.name: Sarah Speaks
last_episode_to_air.overview: Greg Jackson, known to the world as "Onision," discovered YouTube when the platform was still in its infancy. He amassed millions of subscribers with his off-kilter and dark humor, but while his content is twisted, his real life might be more sinister.

name: Onision: In Real Life
overview: The mystery, controversy and alleged criminality surrounding YouTuber Greg "Onision" Jackson, bringing forward new research and revelations about the man that the YouTube community loves to hate.

episodes.name: Banana Power
episodes.overview: Greg Jackson, aka Onision, has become one of YouTube's most controversial figures. After skyrocketing to Internet fame in the mid-2000s, the content creator begins a relationship with an underage fan named Shiloh.

episodes.name: You've Destroyed Me
episodes.overview: The Onision saga continues as the world watches his toxic relationship with Shiloh implode. Before the dust can settle, Onision connects with a new teen fan named Kai, and allegations arise that Greg uses Kai to attract a slew of new, vulnerable victims.

episodes.name: Unmonitored and Chaotic
episodes.overview: Onision's victims begin speaking out, prompting journalist Chris Hansen to enter the arena as law enforcement continues to investigate. Facing a storm of controversy, Onision lashes out against his detractors, trying to save his legacy and freedom.
